      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, logging is a good start, but with the high frequency of these sensor packets, logs might overflow our serial buffer too quickly. \n\nSince we're on bare metal, do you have any advice on how to instrument the heap itself? Like, is there a way to track the total heap usage or catch the exact moment a pointer goes out of scope without a massive logging overhead? I really need to pin down exactly where these bytes are disappearing to.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
